 Load Balancer


 ðŸ”¹ What is a Load Balancer 

A Load Balancer is a cloud component that distributes incoming traffic across multiple servers (VMs).

Instead of sending all users to one server, traffic is shared.



 ðŸ”¹ Why Load Balancer is Needed

 1ï¸âƒ£ High Availability

 If one server fails, traffic is sent to healthy servers
 Application remains available

 2ï¸âƒ£ Scalability

 More users â†’ add more servers
 Load balancer automatically spreads traffic



 ðŸ”¹ How It Works (Simple Flow)


User
 â†“
Load Balancer (Public IP / DNS)
 â†“
VM1   VM2   VM3


Users never access servers directly.



 ðŸ”¹ Common Types)

 Layer 4 (TCP/UDP) â€“ fast, simple
