 ðŸ”¹ Linux Admin Role 

 1ï¸âƒ£ Configure web/application servers

 Ensure web service is running (nginx/apache)
 App must listen on correct port (80/443/8080)
 Firewall must allow traffic from Load Balancer



 2ï¸âƒ£ Health Check Troubleshooting

Load balancer checks server health using:

 HTTP response
 TCP connection
 Custom URL

If server is unhealthy, traffic is stopped.

Linux admin checks:

systemctl status nginx
curl http://localhost/health
ss -tulnp




 ðŸ”¹ Common Problem Scenario

 Website down even though server is running

Check:

 Health check URL correct?
 App responding with HTTP 200?
 Security Group allows traffic from LB?
 OS firewall allows LB traffic?



 ðŸ”¹ Real-Life Example

 3 web servers behind load balancer
 One server crashes
 Users donâ€™t notice any downtime


 
